        <div class="base-aside-card__info self-center pl-1 flex flex-col flex-1">
          <h3 class="base-aside-card__title font-sans text-md font-bold text-color-text relative">
            
<!---->          </h3>

<!---->
            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          My SEO strategy started with a failure, but ultimately earned me $20 million. Here's the full story:

I’ve been working with this client for a year.
A single website that drives $50M in annual revenue.
(Yes, just from that site, he has plenty.)

We had early wins.
But also dips... thanks to Google updates, AI shifts, and legal messiness.

Some weeks were brutal.
But they didn’t freak out.
They didn’t pressure me.

The message was: “Keep going. You’ll find it.”
So I tested, and tested, and tested.

And after 6 months, we cracked it.
I found a way to scale their content using programmatic SEO.
Clean of thin content or indexing problems.

Here’s the result:
📈 From 111k to 215k daily clicks
💰 Roughly $20M in added revenue... just from SEO

The lesson here is always the same:
SEO is trust and patience.

This client invested in SEO, but more importantly, invested in me.

I never received messages like :
"What did the AI tool say this week?"
"I found these keywords please use them"
"How come we lost traffic compared to y'day?" (and it's .5%)

And then there’s the other side…

The ones who will see "wow, results in 6 months? how come they didn't fire him before lol"

The same who are hesitating to invest in SEO…
 …and expecting overnight results?

I think they have a mindset problem.
...And I honestly don't know how they can run a business.

If you're a builder, then SEO shouldn't scare you.
You shouldn't be scared of testing, failing &amp; testing again.
You shouldn't criticize the ones who do.
It should be your thing, since you think like a strategist, right?

Also no, AI won’t change that.

If anything, AI makes it more valuable to have someone who can think clearly, act strategically, and find non-obvious solutions.

Because that’s what actually makes you richer.

♻️ REPOST if you’ve stayed patient, tested like hell, and made it work.
        
            </p>

