            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          Call it AIO, GEO, LLMO or AEO... AI search has new rules for optimization. Is your website ready?

If your team is struggling to catch up with the latest SEO strategies and tactics, this episode is for you.

Generative engines like ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity don’t “rank” pages.
- They extract answers.
- They pull the clearest, most consistent content chunks, and skip the rest.

So if your message is hidden behind tabs, written in brand-speak, or inconsistent across your site and partner pages…

You’re invisible.

In the latest episode of Revenue Boost: A Marketing Podcast, 𝙏𝙝𝙚 𝙉𝙚𝙬 𝙎𝙀𝙊 𝙁𝙧𝙤𝙣𝙩𝙞𝙚𝙧: 𝙃𝙤𝙬 𝙈𝙖𝙧𝙠𝙚𝙩𝙚𝙧𝙨 𝘾𝙖𝙣 𝙒𝙞𝙣 𝙑𝙞𝙨𝙞𝙗𝙞𝙡𝙞𝙩𝙮 𝙞𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝘼𝙜𝙚 𝙤𝙛 𝘼𝙄 I sit down with B2B marketing strategist David Kirkdorffer to unpack:

1) What Generative Engine Optimization (GEO) really means
2) Why LLMs “read” content differently, and how to structure for retrieval
3) The role of off-site consistency, content clarity, and semantic tags
4) A roadmap to align SEO, content, PR, and demand gen for AI visibility

Stay tuned to the end, where David shares what to prioritize when getting started, so you can make real progress even with limited resources.

👇 Comment with how your team is approaching SEO in the age of AI, curious to hear what others are seeing.
        
            </p>

